{
  "texts": [
    "Balcony techniques were employed.",
    "These techniques encompassed statistical models, optimization methods, and boosting approaches.",
    "For instance, the KNN algorithm predicted based on sentence similarity and the k number of nearest sentences.",
    "LR and MNB are statistical models that make predictions by considering the probability of class based on a decision boundary and the frequency of words in sentences, respectively.",
    "Similarly, LR and SVC employed a boundary to predict the class using a features map of words."
  ]
}